{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17644075","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17644075"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:01:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:01:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18034"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18034","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18034"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.2,0,0,0.04,0.76]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10748"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73330"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10748","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10748"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18034"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58801"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"9885"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25076"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25078"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73330","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/73330"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements is correct regarding the deep cervical lymph nodes?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["They form a pericervical collar","They are superficial lymph nodes","They do not receive lymph from the head and neck","They drain lymph from the lower limbs","They are located along the internal jugular vein"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe deep cervical lymph nodes are an important group of lymph nodes located in the neck. They play a crucial role in the lymphatic drainage of the head and neck region.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe deep cervical lymph nodes are located along the \u003Cstrong\u003Einternal jugular vein\u003C/strong\u003E and are responsible for collecting lymph from the head and neck region. They do not form a pericervical collar; this is a feature of the superficial lymph nodes. The deep cervical lymph nodes are not involved in draining lymph from the lower limbs.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The deep cervical lymph nodes are a group of lymph nodes located along the internal jugular vein.","They collect lymph from the head and neck region, including the superficial lymph nodes.","The deep cervical lymph nodes do not form a pericervical collar; this is formed by superficial lymph nodes."],"references":["Fehrenbach, M. J., \u0026 Herring, S. W. (2015). Illustrated Anatomy of the Head and Neck-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, et al. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK534836/","Cramer, G. D., \u0026 Darby, S. A. (2013). Clinical anatomy of the spine, spinal cord, and ANS","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58801"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18034"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58801","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58801"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-23T11:37:37+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-23T11:38: